"fn\">v</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span>)</span>)</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">w</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span>)</span>)</span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Consider `C^n` maps `v : M → E₁` and `v : M → E₂` to vector bundles, over a base map\n`b : M → B`, and bilinear maps `ψ m : E₁ (b m) → E₂ (b m) → E₃ (b m)` depending smoothly on `m`.\nOne can apply `ψ  m` to `v m` and `w m`, and the resulting map is `C^n`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/VectorBundle/Hom.html#ContMDiff.clm_bundle_apply₂","kind":"theorem","line":422,"name":"ContMDiff.clm_bundle_apply₂","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/VectorBundle/Hom.lean#L422-L433"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Geometry/Manifold/VectorBundle/Hom.html#ContMDiffOn.clm_bundle_apply₂\"><span class=\"name\">ContMDiffOn</span>.<span class=\"name\">clm_bundle_apply₂</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">B</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F₁</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F₂</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_4}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">F₃</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_5}</span></span>\n</span><span class